{"type":"message","id":"4c6dad2a","parentId":"13898b7d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:07:24.686Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nz6783931cnk_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 130614\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: experiments/strategy_c_hybrid_scoring.py (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent work:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. The CFI Compression Experiment was just completed with key findings\r\n3. The next pending action is the \"Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n4. Key insight: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe most logical next step is to run the hybrid scoring experiment that was identified as the next action. This involves:\r\n1. Creating a new scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n2. Testing it against the same 200-pulse dataset\r\n3. Comparing to the previous binary threshold results\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment script or document that implements this hybrid scoring approach. Let me look at what exists from the previous experiment.\r\n\r\nThe previous experiment was documented in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. I should either:\r\n1. Create a new experiment script that tests the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Update the synthesis document with the new experiment plan\r\n\r\nGiven the \"file edits\" preference and the concrete nature of the task, I'll create a new experiment file that implements the hybrid scoring and runs it against the pulse data.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and create the experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified a concrete scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120). This hybrid approach addresses the constant-format problem by penalizing both high-frequency metaprogramming tokens AND low-CFI noise.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a PowerShell experiment script that implements the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring and runs it against the existing pulse corpus to validate the approach.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Generated: 2026-03-24\r\n# Based on: CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nValidate hypothesis: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) outperforms binary CFI threshold alone\r\n\r\n## Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) * min(1, freq(T) / 120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Scoring Interpretation\r\n| Score Range | Interpretation |\r\n|-------------|----------------|\r\n| � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120) | TRUE semantic token (causal + informative) |\r\n| � 0.5 AND freq � 120 | Format artifact (CFI inflated by repetition) |\r\n| < 0.5 AND freq < 3 | Low confidence / new token |\r\n| < 0.5 AND freq � 3 | Noise / low informativeness |\r\n\r\n### Expected Behavior\r\n- \"Phase 1\": CFI=0.96, freq=136  score = 0.96 * 1.0 = 0.96 (penalized by freq cap)\r\n- \"research\": CFI=0.65, freq=45  score = 0.65 * 0.375 = 0.244\r\n- \"for next instantiation\": CFI=1.00, freq=160  score = 1.0 * 1.0 = 1.0 (caught by freq filter)\r\n- \"pulse\": CFI=1.00, freq=160  score = 1.0 (caught by freq filter)\r\n\r\n### Test Plan\r\n1. Load all pulse files from `pulses/`\r\n2. Compute CFI(T) and freq(T) for all tokens\r\n3. Apply hybrid score formula\r\n4. Compare token ranking to:\r\n   - Pure CFI � 0.5 threshold (previous Strategy A)\r\n   - Binary CFI � 0.7 AND freq < 60 (previous Strategy B)\r\n5. Output: Top-50 tokens by hybrid score with all metrics\r\n\r\n### Metrics to Compare\r\n- Precision @ top-50 tokens (manual assessment)\r\n- Recall of known research terms\r\n- Separation of \"constant format\" vs \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\n## Execution\r\n```powershell\r\n# Compute hybrid scores for all tokens across pulses\r\n# Output: research/HYB